<subSubSection id="C3119890DF4AFF8B3C9CD5DDF0D3FF21" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB4CB1BDF4AFF8B3C9CD5DDF0D3FF21" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B97F1709DF4AFF8B3C9CD5DDF66AFF6F" bold="true" box="[198,512,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—This hybrid occurs in the Vacaria municipality in 
<collectingRegion id="49CF05F9DF4AFF8B3838D5D2F155FF6C" box="[1122,1343,152,178]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, next to the Pelotas River. We located only one individual, growing on basaltic rock outcrops within an 
<taxonomicName id="4C0BB098DF4AFF8B397FD5F4F1F6FF06" box="[1317,1436,190,216]" class="Pinopsida" family="Araucariaceae" genus="Araucaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="3" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Araucaria</taxonomicName>
forest, close to streams or in shaded habitats, between 600 and 
<quantity id="4CF366FEDF4AFF8B3F22D5AFF7A9FF21" box="[888,963,229,255]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
in elevation (
<figureCitation id="1330D79EDF4AFF8B3839D5AFF0C1FF21" box="[1123,1195,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1974,1995]" captionTargetBox="[201,1387,772,1955]" captionTargetId="figure-283@2.[201,1387,772,1955]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of Sinningia macrostachya, S. lineata and S. × vacariensis in South America, showing the overlapping area. Blue circle. S. macrostachya. Red triangle. S. lineata. Pink lozenge. S. × vacariensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5079351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5079351/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3119890DF4AFF8B3C9CD441F5F3FE96" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB4CB1BDF4AFF8B3C9CD441F5F3FE96" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B97F1709DF4AFF8B3C9CD441F51EFEFB" bold="true" box="[198,372,267,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The name of the nothospecies is derived from the municipality “Vacaria” where the plant was first encountered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
